WEBVTT

01:04.981 --> 01:07.901
EPISODE 10

01:51.569 --> 01:52.821
What... What's going on?

01:53.321 --> 01:55.240
That's what I want to ask you guys.

01:55.323 --> 01:58.576
He said he had something to tell me
and got down on his knees like this.

01:59.035 --> 02:02.831
Gosh, Jun-hui.
Whatever it is, you can tell me.

02:02.914 --> 02:06.000
Why are you acting like
you've done something wrong?

02:12.048 --> 02:13.091
What's going on?

02:13.842 --> 02:15.385
You guys...

02:16.136 --> 02:18.096
Why the heck are you two being like this?

02:24.102 --> 02:25.145
Hang on.

02:27.647 --> 02:28.690
Gosh, no way.

02:31.484 --> 02:33.486
The two of you...

02:35.155 --> 02:37.282
It's not what I'm thinking, right?

02:37.782 --> 02:38.908
Right?

02:40.535 --> 02:42.203
- Mom.
- Yes.

02:43.288 --> 02:44.247
I'm sorry, Ms. Kim.

02:46.416 --> 02:49.043
My goodness, how am I supposed to...

02:49.127 --> 02:50.837
- Gosh, this...
- Mom, are you okay?

02:50.920 --> 02:53.506
- I can't believe this.
- Mom, try to calm down, okay?

02:54.090 --> 02:58.636
What? Did you... Did you know?

02:59.929 --> 03:02.432
Well... Yes.

03:02.515 --> 03:04.100
My goodness!

03:05.101 --> 03:07.186
When are you going to come to your senses?

03:07.270 --> 03:09.022
You should be focusing on
getting your degree.

03:09.105 --> 03:11.649
Why do you always waste your time
on playing games?

03:11.941 --> 03:13.943
You should be studying hard right now.

03:14.027 --> 03:16.404
Why are you wasting your time
on other things?

03:17.113 --> 03:18.907
Mom, why are you taking it out on him?

03:18.990 --> 03:20.783
Exactly. What did I do--

03:20.867 --> 03:23.536
Do you think you are in a position
to talk back to me?

03:24.120 --> 03:26.581
How could you disappoint me like this?

03:27.332 --> 03:29.125
Follow me inside. Hurry up.

03:29.292 --> 03:30.418
Mom.

03:31.461 --> 03:33.379
- Mom.
- Hurry up!

03:36.132 --> 03:38.009
But we need to finish talking about...

04:13.169 --> 04:15.713
How could you keep it from me?
How could you?

04:15.964 --> 04:17.590
Do you want to ruin your sister's life?

04:17.674 --> 04:21.177
- What are you talking about?
- Shut your mouth. Shut it!

04:22.762 --> 04:26.015
Listen to me carefully.

04:26.307 --> 04:28.101
Don't hang out with Jun-hui from now on.

04:30.061 --> 04:31.479
I can't believe this.

04:32.188 --> 04:33.273
My gosh.

04:40.613 --> 04:41.739
Are you leaving?

04:42.740 --> 04:44.200
I think I should.

05:08.224 --> 05:09.225
I'm sorry.

05:10.059 --> 05:13.229
I'm the one who should be sorry.
I should've discussed it with you first.

05:14.522 --> 05:18.276
Just listen to whatever
your mom has to say, okay?

05:20.653 --> 05:21.821
Don't talk back to her.

05:22.280 --> 05:24.782
I don't want you to go through any trouble
when I'm not with you.

05:25.533 --> 05:26.576
Okay?

05:32.332 --> 05:33.374
You should go inside.

05:33.833 --> 05:35.084
Why?

05:36.419 --> 05:38.254
I know how to get to the first floor.

05:43.593 --> 05:44.719
I'll call you.

05:49.891 --> 05:50.892
You should go.

06:33.101 --> 06:34.644
- I'm going to kill this brat.
- Mom!

06:34.727 --> 06:36.813
- Come over here.
- Mom, don't. Stop.

06:37.313 --> 06:39.607
- Let go of me!
- Just tell her that you're sorry.

06:39.690 --> 06:41.275
I didn't do anything wrong.

06:42.443 --> 06:45.196
Are you out of your mind?
How can you be so brazen right now?

06:45.321 --> 06:46.823
I get that you're angry,

06:47.323 --> 06:49.617
but how could you
just ignore him like that?

06:50.076 --> 06:51.786
It was Jun-hui, for goodness' sake.

06:52.161 --> 06:54.205
How could you ignore him like that?

06:55.540 --> 06:58.626
My gosh, I'm the one who wants to ask you
why it has to be Jun-hui

06:58.709 --> 07:00.586
of all people.

07:01.045 --> 07:02.213
Why can't it be him?

07:02.421 --> 07:03.714
What's the reason?

07:04.090 --> 07:05.675
Because you knew him since he was little?

07:06.008 --> 07:07.885
Because you thought of him as a son?

07:08.261 --> 07:09.512
So what?

07:09.595 --> 07:12.098
What difference does that make?
What's the big deal?

07:12.181 --> 07:13.891
This is not the time to talk back to her!

07:14.517 --> 07:17.520
I really can't believe you right now.

07:17.770 --> 07:19.439
You're completely out of your mind,

07:19.522 --> 07:21.315
- you brat!
- Mom!

07:21.482 --> 07:24.110
How could you choose him of all people?

07:24.277 --> 07:26.112
You think it's not a big deal?

07:26.237 --> 07:27.947
This is a disaster!

07:28.906 --> 07:32.452
I didn't choose him. He chose me.

07:32.785 --> 07:34.662
I was lucky enough to be chosen.

07:35.788 --> 07:36.956
You have no idea

07:37.206 --> 07:39.167
how much I'm in love with him.

07:39.250 --> 07:41.419
- Have you gone mad?
- Mom, please.

07:41.502 --> 07:43.212
- You!
- Mom, please!

07:43.296 --> 07:45.256
You'd better listen to me
while I'm being nice.

07:45.465 --> 07:47.508
Don't even dream of seeing him ever again.

07:49.260 --> 07:51.137
Don't even expect that I'll listen to you.

07:51.345 --> 07:52.555
I'm going to date him.

07:53.139 --> 07:55.433
I'm going to date him no matter what.

07:55.516 --> 07:57.310
- You little...
- Mom!

07:57.393 --> 07:58.853
- Let go of me. Let go.
- Mom.

07:59.020 --> 08:01.397
- Mom, calm down!
- Let go of me!

08:04.150 --> 08:05.318
How dare you talk back to me?

08:05.818 --> 08:07.361
How dare you raise your voice to me?

08:08.154 --> 08:11.240
You should be ashamed of yourself!
How dare you be so brazen?

08:11.949 --> 08:13.743
What? You're going to date him?

08:14.202 --> 08:15.786
Do you think you're making any sense?

08:15.870 --> 08:17.246
He's your brother.

08:17.914 --> 08:19.540
How is he my brother?

08:19.707 --> 08:21.209
Did you give birth to him?

08:22.668 --> 08:25.004
Do you think that's the only thing
that matters?

08:25.379 --> 08:27.840
I thought of him like my own,
and that makes him my son.

08:28.049 --> 08:29.550
To your dad and I,

08:29.634 --> 08:31.844
he's our son just like Seung-ho is.

08:31.928 --> 08:33.262
I don't think of him that way.

08:33.346 --> 08:36.641
To me, Jun-hui is just a man I like.

08:38.059 --> 08:39.101
You little...

08:39.435 --> 08:41.229
What? A man you like?

08:41.854 --> 08:45.566
How... How dare you?
You should be ashamed of yourself.

08:47.985 --> 08:50.530
Fine, keep acting that way.

08:51.239 --> 08:53.699
Okay. Let's see who wins.

09:03.584 --> 09:05.294
Did you think it would be easy?

09:06.504 --> 09:08.965
Fighting Mom will be no good for you guys.

09:09.674 --> 09:11.217
Don't you know who you are dealing with?

09:12.510 --> 09:14.679
Mom is not the type
to let her children have their way.

11:35.069 --> 11:36.529
I just wanted to check up on you.

11:38.114 --> 11:39.198
Don't cry.

12:29.331 --> 12:30.708
- Be quiet.
- What?

12:32.585 --> 12:35.629
Mom found out about Jun-hui and Jin-a.
It was a mess.

12:40.134 --> 12:41.802
Let me take care of it.

12:41.969 --> 12:42.970
Mi-yeon.

12:43.095 --> 12:44.597
My goodness.

13:02.239 --> 13:04.158
I already approved of

13:04.241 --> 13:06.410
their relationship.

13:08.537 --> 13:09.747
Mom, here's some water.

13:09.830 --> 13:12.291
Both of them are grown-ups,
and they are dating.

13:16.253 --> 13:17.421
What's the problem?

13:18.672 --> 13:20.674
What's he saying?

13:20.758 --> 13:21.592
You approved of what?

13:21.675 --> 13:23.677
Why? What's there not to approve of?

13:23.802 --> 13:25.638
They're in love.

13:26.305 --> 13:28.641
So why stop them?

13:28.724 --> 13:30.976
Does this mean everyone knew about them

13:31.060 --> 13:33.187
except for me?

13:35.189 --> 13:38.609
You must be upset
for being the last one to find out.

13:39.109 --> 13:41.111
I was the first to find out.

13:41.195 --> 13:43.405
- I'm going to rip his mouth apart!
- Mom!

13:45.824 --> 13:47.701
- Mom, are you okay?
- Are you okay?

13:48.285 --> 13:50.746
- My gosh, this isn't good.
- I think I'm going to die.

13:51.205 --> 13:52.706
Let me see.

13:53.541 --> 13:55.292
I didn't cry.

13:56.585 --> 13:57.753
I'm telling the truth.

13:58.671 --> 14:01.006
We agreed to talk about it later.

14:02.299 --> 14:06.011
I think my mom acted that way
because she was really surprised

14:06.095 --> 14:07.638
and taken aback.

14:10.182 --> 14:11.767
Yes, I know.

14:14.144 --> 14:15.145
Yes.

14:17.690 --> 14:20.901
You shouldn't feel
too upset about it either.

14:21.193 --> 14:22.778
I hope you understand.

14:24.697 --> 14:26.991
- Yes.
- Jin-a!

14:29.285 --> 14:30.327
Come outside.

14:34.081 --> 14:35.207
I'll call you back.

14:48.929 --> 14:49.972
My gosh.

14:51.724 --> 14:53.475
What are you doing? Go get the car.

14:53.851 --> 14:56.186
Actually, I had some beer a while ago.

14:58.105 --> 14:59.148
Wait here.

15:03.152 --> 15:06.322
You're completely useless.

15:30.137 --> 15:31.305
We won't be of much help.

15:32.890 --> 15:33.933
Do you think so?

15:49.073 --> 15:50.908
You should have been born a daughter.

15:52.743 --> 15:55.037
You aren't the most reliable person
in the family either.

15:57.331 --> 15:59.124
It sucks to be a man.

16:00.417 --> 16:01.669
I know.

16:06.799 --> 16:09.677
I won't use this to my advantage
to make you approve of my relationship.

16:09.760 --> 16:10.886
So don't worry.

16:10.970 --> 16:12.805
Stop acting like you're being generous.

16:13.347 --> 16:15.849
You're in no place to be picky.

16:17.142 --> 16:18.894
This happened because of you!

16:21.105 --> 16:22.648
Okay, I get it.

16:25.150 --> 16:26.193
- Try to--
- My gosh.

16:26.276 --> 16:28.362
Hang in there. I'll be gentle.

16:36.620 --> 16:38.038
Goodness.

17:15.826 --> 17:16.994
- Can we leave?
- Yes.

17:33.761 --> 17:34.595
My gosh.

17:36.096 --> 17:38.974
What would we have done without Jin-a?

17:40.350 --> 17:43.228
She took care of everything perfectly.

17:45.355 --> 17:47.274
My daughter is the best.

17:49.359 --> 17:52.029
She's not lacking in any way.

17:53.072 --> 17:55.824
She is extremely trustworthy.

17:56.867 --> 17:58.202
I'll kick you out of the car.

18:00.621 --> 18:02.414
You are no better than your dad.

18:03.373 --> 18:05.042
I didn't even do anything.

18:05.417 --> 18:07.836
Why did you tag along
if you weren't going to do anything?

18:12.257 --> 18:13.926
You said it yourself.

18:14.134 --> 18:16.095
Don't use this as your opportunity
to call it even.

18:18.388 --> 18:19.932
All right.

18:34.905 --> 18:35.948
Why are you doing this?

18:36.156 --> 18:37.241
Don't you already know?

18:38.158 --> 18:39.576
I wouldn't have asked if I knew.

18:40.202 --> 18:41.453
Sleep on the couch!

19:07.271 --> 19:08.939
What did I do wrong?

19:09.982 --> 19:11.441
It's all my fault.

19:15.237 --> 19:17.030
Don't fight your mom.

19:17.156 --> 19:19.449
She will come at you harder if you do.

19:19.867 --> 19:21.410
Neither should you.

19:21.493 --> 19:22.786
You always say unnecessary things

19:22.870 --> 19:25.038
when you know
it's only going to get you in trouble.

19:26.623 --> 19:27.916
It's fun.

19:33.005 --> 19:34.089
You know,

19:35.549 --> 19:37.176
it won't be easy for your mom
to accept it.

19:38.343 --> 19:41.430
Still, you shouldn't resent her
or hate her.

19:42.347 --> 19:43.515
I already do.

19:44.433 --> 19:47.102
You know she always wants
the best for you.

19:49.438 --> 19:51.106
It's not like I don't know that.

19:56.069 --> 19:58.071
Let's try harder, both of us.

20:05.078 --> 20:08.290
You don't seem to get together with others
after work as often these days.

20:09.458 --> 20:11.960
You rarely join us. Why do you care?

20:12.336 --> 20:14.087
I didn't miss out on purpose.

20:14.254 --> 20:16.215
I always had a prior commitment.

20:17.174 --> 20:18.425
Why don't you get together much?

20:19.927 --> 20:22.095
Things aren't looking so great these days.

20:22.554 --> 20:23.555
Good morning.

20:32.147 --> 20:33.148
- Good morning.
- What is it?

20:49.706 --> 20:51.041
Why are you still out here?

20:52.960 --> 20:55.045
What happened between you and Mr. Nam?

20:57.172 --> 20:58.257
What is it?

20:58.590 --> 21:01.301
Why did you become so nosy
all of a sudden?

21:01.426 --> 21:02.261
I mean,

21:03.053 --> 21:04.721
you two used to get along very well.

21:05.555 --> 21:08.642
An easygoing person like you
would not act this way

21:08.725 --> 21:11.520
unless they have a good reason to.

21:14.022 --> 21:15.482
You are a good judge of character.

21:16.358 --> 21:17.359
The thing is...

21:19.111 --> 21:22.072
- He has been stressing me out...
- Go on.

21:24.241 --> 21:26.243
Gosh, never mind.

21:29.705 --> 21:33.458
I should buy you a drink
at someplace nice.

21:34.334 --> 21:35.669
You mean it? Seriously?

21:35.794 --> 21:37.587
I'm your colleague.

21:38.463 --> 21:40.132
I should be there for you
when you need me.

21:42.301 --> 21:45.470
Where do you mean by "someplace nice"?
Do you have a place in mind?

21:45.554 --> 21:46.722
Of course.

21:47.556 --> 21:48.390
Where?

21:52.394 --> 21:54.438
Ms. Yoon doesn't come to the office
often nowadays.

21:54.688 --> 21:55.772
Is she too busy?

21:56.565 --> 21:58.400
The store is keeping her busy,

21:58.483 --> 22:00.319
but I'm sure she is also busy
with other things.

22:01.987 --> 22:03.363
You knew?

22:04.489 --> 22:05.490
You too?

22:06.450 --> 22:08.327
Is there something I should know?

22:09.328 --> 22:11.413
- Dong-u, we're going to be late. Let's go.
- Well...

22:18.086 --> 22:19.046
Why didn't you tell me?

22:19.671 --> 22:20.922
Did she tell you not to tell me?

22:22.716 --> 22:24.760
So, it did bother her.

22:24.885 --> 22:26.344
Then why did she say she isn't sorry?

22:26.428 --> 22:27.721
Let's begin the meeting.

22:27.804 --> 22:30.098
And what else did she say?

22:30.557 --> 22:32.559
Did she tell you
how she'll make it up to me?

22:32.642 --> 22:35.228
- Who do you mean?
- Were you even listening?

22:35.479 --> 22:37.689
You said Jin-a told you
about her boyfriend.

22:38.398 --> 22:40.317
I heard it
from the person directly involved.

22:40.400 --> 22:41.401
Yes, that is--

22:44.571 --> 22:45.489
Who do you mean?

22:47.574 --> 22:48.700
Mr. Seo.

22:48.784 --> 22:52.287
I asked him if he knows
who her boyfriend is, and he went,

22:53.830 --> 22:55.040
"It's me."

23:15.435 --> 23:17.813
Mom injured her arm.

23:17.896 --> 23:19.898
So I think I should go home early
for the time being.

23:25.403 --> 23:26.321
Gosh.

23:26.571 --> 23:29.866
Okay, but slow down.
You'll upset your stomach.

23:30.784 --> 23:33.411
I have to go back to the store.
We are short-handed today.

23:34.663 --> 23:36.414
I picked a girlfriend who is too busy.

23:37.749 --> 23:39.376
I know I'm a handful.

23:39.751 --> 23:40.752
You are not. I am.

23:43.672 --> 23:44.881
Why do you say that?

23:46.758 --> 23:47.759
Never mind.

23:52.514 --> 23:54.808
Forget it. I was just saying.

23:55.642 --> 23:57.561
Don't say something like that.

24:00.188 --> 24:01.690
I put you through trouble, you know.

24:01.773 --> 24:05.110
That was because of my mom.
Why would you take the blame?

24:06.486 --> 24:08.738
You were the one who told me
not to put myself down.

24:10.365 --> 24:11.825
I must have looked really stupid.

24:13.160 --> 24:14.744
Is that what you thought of me all along?

24:15.203 --> 24:16.621
I always thought you were pretty.

24:17.831 --> 24:19.166
Gosh.

24:20.250 --> 24:21.793
I fall for flattery too easily.

24:23.170 --> 24:25.714
I wouldn't have been able to win you over
if you weren't like that.

24:27.507 --> 24:29.259
Anyway, don't you ever say that--

24:29.342 --> 24:30.969
- I won't.
- Don't you ever.

24:31.219 --> 24:32.804
I won't. I'll never say such a thing.

24:32.888 --> 24:34.681
Don't you ever, all right?

24:40.228 --> 24:41.479
Slow down.

24:49.738 --> 24:50.947
This is too big.

24:52.824 --> 24:53.867
I'm done.

25:00.457 --> 25:01.583
Take your time.

25:14.763 --> 25:15.972
Welcome.

25:18.808 --> 25:20.393
What would you like to order?

25:23.063 --> 25:25.357
- Get the upper left side.
- Yes, ma'am.

25:25.815 --> 25:27.067
Use this.

25:27.859 --> 25:29.903
Ms. Kim, are you hurt?

25:29.986 --> 25:31.571
- How did you--
- It's nothing serious.

25:31.988 --> 25:35.242
It doesn't seem like it.
You should've been careful.

25:36.368 --> 25:37.661
Let's talk inside.

25:48.588 --> 25:50.131
Even you knew?

25:51.800 --> 25:53.927
It hasn't been long since I found out.

25:54.344 --> 25:56.846
Words can't express how shocked I was.

25:58.556 --> 25:59.849
But it already happened.

26:00.725 --> 26:02.477
We should wish them the best.

26:02.811 --> 26:03.812
How can you...

26:05.563 --> 26:07.649
That's not how we should handle this.

26:08.733 --> 26:11.861
Jin-a and Jun-hui are practically family.

26:12.237 --> 26:13.530
I know that.

26:14.322 --> 26:16.449
- But what can we do when they're in love?
- Gosh!

26:17.284 --> 26:18.910
Just the thought of it makes me cringe.

26:21.997 --> 26:23.373
I'm being like this

26:23.456 --> 26:26.626
because I think of Jun-hui as my own son.

26:28.545 --> 26:30.380
You should think about it carefully.

26:30.839 --> 26:33.341
This isn't something we can take lightly.

26:35.427 --> 26:38.096
Jun-hui is a good kid in every aspect,
I know.

26:39.431 --> 26:42.392
I know I have a tendency to judge people
by their family background and such.

26:42.809 --> 26:44.311
But we are talking about Jun-hui here.

26:44.644 --> 26:46.187
I would never do that with him.

26:47.814 --> 26:50.191
- You shouldn't.
- Of course, I shouldn't.

26:51.443 --> 26:52.694
Don't get me wrong.

26:53.528 --> 26:57.574
They've known each other for so long.
I just think they are confused

26:57.657 --> 26:59.451
and making a huge mistake.

26:59.534 --> 27:00.744
Speaking of which...

27:01.911 --> 27:04.831
Do you really think
they reached this decision

27:04.914 --> 27:07.334
based on rational reasons?

27:07.625 --> 27:08.793
Is that what you think?

27:09.836 --> 27:11.629
I have not thought about that.

27:11.713 --> 27:12.881
I knew it.

27:15.383 --> 27:16.885
No wonder.

27:17.594 --> 27:20.764
I knew it was unlike you
to make such a bad judgment.

27:23.099 --> 27:24.392
Gyeong-seon.

27:25.060 --> 27:26.811
You're his older sister.

27:27.437 --> 27:28.646
What does that make you?

27:29.064 --> 27:30.899
You're practically his parent.

27:31.900 --> 27:33.818
Jun-hui's still young,

27:33.943 --> 27:37.113
so you need to guide him
toward the right path, right?

27:38.823 --> 27:41.076
Don't you remember
what you always said to me?

27:42.619 --> 27:44.454
You always said
you would take responsibility

27:44.537 --> 27:47.415
and guide Jun-hui to the right path
until the very end.

27:48.708 --> 27:51.753
I didn't know this was putting
his whole life at risk.

27:53.797 --> 27:56.383
There's nothing grand about life.

27:57.592 --> 27:59.344
It's just a process

28:00.053 --> 28:03.181
of pursuing righteousness
by trying to take all the right steps.

28:03.848 --> 28:07.352
That's why taking a single wrong step

28:07.435 --> 28:08.812
can't get one's life back on track.

28:12.816 --> 28:15.693
Well, there's no need for me
to explain this to you.

28:16.611 --> 28:19.447
I know you are with me on this.

28:20.740 --> 28:22.909
We're very much alike, you know.

28:23.535 --> 28:24.577
Don't you agree?

28:58.987 --> 29:02.615
Bus number 740

29:03.032 --> 29:06.411
and 7726 will be arriving soon.

29:21.926 --> 29:23.428
My goodness.

29:38.443 --> 29:39.652
Yes.

30:31.412 --> 30:32.705
Did you go somewhere?

30:34.666 --> 30:36.709
- Where were you?
- Help me take this off.

30:40.213 --> 30:42.382
Sit down for a second.

30:47.178 --> 30:48.930
I met Gyeong-seon.

30:49.097 --> 30:50.223
My gosh.

30:50.849 --> 30:52.851
What's that reaction?

30:53.309 --> 30:56.646
How could you be so nonchalant about this?

30:57.647 --> 31:00.149
Jin-a's your one-and-only daughter.

31:01.109 --> 31:03.695
Are you okay with her dating Jun-hui?

31:04.779 --> 31:07.699
What if I am and what if I'm not?
They're already in love.

31:07.782 --> 31:10.660
You're being overly positive again.

31:11.744 --> 31:14.998
Some people say
it's better to have no in-laws

31:15.248 --> 31:17.667
than to have difficult in-laws.

31:17.917 --> 31:20.086
But that's not the case for Jun-hui.

31:20.753 --> 31:23.840
He'll have to take care of
all his step-siblings.

31:24.632 --> 31:26.801
That means they'll become
Jin-a's responsibility.

31:26.968 --> 31:28.928
Are you going to let them get married?

31:29.012 --> 31:30.013
Gosh.

31:30.889 --> 31:32.348
You need to filter what you say.

31:34.267 --> 31:36.227
Listen to me carefully.

31:37.353 --> 31:39.814
Stop trying to support
your daughter unconditionally

31:39.898 --> 31:42.150
and start trying
to become a better parent.

31:42.317 --> 31:44.736
Just think about
what's best for Jin-a, okay?

31:45.278 --> 31:48.197
Your daughter's life depends on this.

31:50.199 --> 31:52.744
How can they not know
that they aren't good enough for us?

32:12.096 --> 32:13.139
What's this?

32:15.850 --> 32:16.976
Go wash your hands.

32:23.191 --> 32:24.192
Here.

32:25.193 --> 32:26.945
Eat up.

32:27.070 --> 32:28.404
It's your favorite dish.

32:29.530 --> 32:32.367
Let me know why you're doing this
before I eat.

32:34.410 --> 32:36.329
What do you mean?

32:37.580 --> 32:39.165
I just wanted to cook these

32:39.999 --> 32:42.919
because I was craving a variety of dishes.

32:44.045 --> 32:45.213
You can't fool me.

32:47.090 --> 32:49.801
Well, then don't ask.

32:50.259 --> 32:51.386
Just eat up.

33:00.478 --> 33:02.105
Let's try harder

33:03.147 --> 33:05.775
and live a better life.
Let's keep our heads up.

33:21.082 --> 33:22.709
Your cooking gets better and better.

33:23.334 --> 33:24.419
You should get married.

33:26.921 --> 33:28.089
Don't make me laugh.

33:28.172 --> 33:30.383
You can't even survive a day without me.

33:30.758 --> 33:31.926
Don't use me as your excuse.

33:32.093 --> 33:33.720
You are the one who can't live without me.

33:34.470 --> 33:35.930
Yes, you're right.

33:37.181 --> 33:38.433
So you'd better stay by my side.

33:39.183 --> 33:40.476
I'll kill you if you don't.

33:40.560 --> 33:42.270
Then be nice to me while I'm still around.

33:43.187 --> 33:44.439
How can I be nicer?

33:45.398 --> 33:47.900
You can never find another sister like me.

33:49.777 --> 33:50.903
It'd be a disaster if I do.

33:51.279 --> 33:52.864
You alone are too much to handle already.

33:53.364 --> 33:55.658
- You little...
- Because you make me so happy.

33:55.742 --> 33:57.744
You've brought so much happiness
into my life.

34:01.289 --> 34:02.331
It's delicious.

34:02.707 --> 34:04.083
- Eat up.
- Okay.

34:11.215 --> 34:13.092
If you take your medicine
right after you eat,

34:13.176 --> 34:14.844
your stomach will hurt less.

34:18.181 --> 34:19.766
- I'll do it.
- Forget it.

34:19.849 --> 34:20.892
Just give it to me.

34:36.407 --> 34:38.076
You should've kept it a secret,

34:38.159 --> 34:39.869
but it seems like you've told everyone.

34:39.952 --> 34:41.162
Even Gyeong-seon knew.

34:44.040 --> 34:45.166
What did you say?

34:46.042 --> 34:47.293
What did you say to her?

34:48.044 --> 34:49.921
There was no need to say much.

34:50.004 --> 34:51.255
She's quick-witted.

34:51.339 --> 34:52.548
She's not dumb like you.

34:59.430 --> 35:00.765
I'm an adult.

35:01.766 --> 35:03.142
I can date

35:03.226 --> 35:05.520
and get married
without my parents' permission.

35:08.981 --> 35:09.982
Is that so?

35:10.399 --> 35:13.402
Fine, let's see how things turn out.

35:24.914 --> 35:26.415
Stay still.

35:27.333 --> 35:29.210
You might regret it later.

35:32.380 --> 35:35.466
I'm not the type to regret anything.

35:47.311 --> 35:50.231
My gosh, stay still. You'll get hurt.

35:53.067 --> 35:54.235
You're going to sleep already?

35:54.944 --> 35:58.447
Yes, I'm so tired
from doing the housework.

35:59.198 --> 36:00.491
You only washed the dishes.

36:01.033 --> 36:04.120
I folded all the laundry,
and I even took out the trash.

36:04.996 --> 36:06.038
You did a great job.

36:06.372 --> 36:09.584
I know that, so cut me some slack today.

36:10.334 --> 36:12.545
Okay. You should go to sleep then.

36:13.004 --> 36:15.006
Okay, I'll call you tomorrow.

36:15.214 --> 36:16.215
Is that all?

36:16.883 --> 36:18.009
My gosh.

36:18.426 --> 36:19.468
"My gosh"?

36:20.094 --> 36:24.473
Okay, fine. I love you so much.

37:10.186 --> 37:11.229
I'm sorry.

37:12.230 --> 37:13.564
Why are you sorry?

37:15.650 --> 37:18.236
Gosh, this is so annoying.
Why can't I stop crying?

37:26.702 --> 37:30.498
Gyeong-seon, what can I do for you?

37:31.415 --> 37:33.042
Don't bother doing anything.

37:36.337 --> 37:38.965
Should I make you laugh?

37:39.340 --> 37:42.093
Gosh, don't bother. It's fine.

37:42.176 --> 37:43.761
What are you going to do?

37:44.011 --> 37:46.347
- You already know what I'm going to do.
- Hey, stop.

37:46.430 --> 37:47.431
No, don't.

37:59.485 --> 38:02.947
My gosh, what's wrong with you?
You're so embarrassing.

40:19.166 --> 40:22.753
Yeong-in asked you to gather evidence?

40:23.504 --> 40:26.882
Yes. I contemplated on
whether I should tell you or not.

40:27.508 --> 40:30.302
But I felt like you should know.

40:32.430 --> 40:35.391
She's not the type
to ask for evidence without a plan.

40:36.517 --> 40:39.645
I have a lot of meetings
outside of the office,

40:39.770 --> 40:42.523
so I rarely interact
with the female employees.

40:42.815 --> 40:45.860
And I also keep my distance
from the male employees.

40:45.943 --> 40:49.947
So I guess she thought
no one would be suspicious of me

40:50.030 --> 40:51.740
even when I approach them.

40:54.368 --> 40:57.163
- If you don't want me to do it...
- Do it.

41:00.458 --> 41:02.918
Yeong-in must be really determined.

41:17.308 --> 41:18.309
Have a seat.

41:26.692 --> 41:28.360
I want you to do something for me.

41:29.945 --> 41:32.948
I want you to gather evidence
regarding all the unfair treatments

41:33.699 --> 41:37.453
toward the female employees,
not just regarding sexual harassment

41:37.912 --> 41:39.330
but also regarding work.

41:43.918 --> 41:47.463
I chose you two because you guys
answered the survey most honestly.

41:48.881 --> 41:50.758
I thought it was anonymous.

41:51.759 --> 41:54.345
Just think that you couldn't hide from me.

41:54.803 --> 41:55.930
Any other questions?

41:56.847 --> 41:58.557
Is the survey not enough?

42:00.100 --> 42:02.478
The participation rate is too low,

42:03.312 --> 42:05.814
and we are not sure
if what they wrote is actually true.

42:06.899 --> 42:08.609
How do we get evidence
on the male employees?

42:09.985 --> 42:11.445
I will take care of it.

42:12.279 --> 42:14.323
Are you saying you'll seek
resolution for complaints

42:14.406 --> 42:16.325
only if they can be backed
by hard evidence?

42:17.284 --> 42:20.329
Yes, for now. And I'm hoping
that the unreported assailants

42:20.538 --> 42:23.249
will end up turning themselves in.

42:25.209 --> 42:26.835
But I might be asking for too much.

42:28.963 --> 42:31.340
Chat history and text messages?

42:33.717 --> 42:35.678
I'm hoping it ends there.

42:36.845 --> 42:38.597
I hope there isn't anything worse...

42:40.891 --> 42:42.476
I don't even want to think about it.

43:00.327 --> 43:01.704
Come in.

43:06.959 --> 43:08.794
Mr. Nam, here's the sales report.

43:15.593 --> 43:17.052
The sales report?

43:20.598 --> 43:24.101
Ms. Kang, how long have you worked
as a supervisor?

43:24.184 --> 43:25.769
It's my seventh year.

43:26.520 --> 43:27.605
Already?

43:27.938 --> 43:30.524
How's the work?

43:32.234 --> 43:33.902
I'm used to everything now.

43:38.699 --> 43:41.076
With your experience and competence,

43:44.872 --> 43:48.167
don't you think it's time for you
to get a promotion?

43:55.090 --> 43:58.677
There are a lot of female employees
in our company,

44:00.387 --> 44:02.181
so it might seem like
no one really stands out.

44:04.058 --> 44:05.309
But how should I put this?

44:06.810 --> 44:10.397
There's always the one who stands out.
Don't you agree?

44:12.941 --> 44:14.943
I'll take that as a compliment.

44:15.069 --> 44:16.445
Gosh, of course.

44:17.821 --> 44:19.198
But you see,

44:20.449 --> 44:23.827
the circumstances are quite difficult.

44:25.371 --> 44:27.706
Picking just one person to support

44:28.582 --> 44:30.000
isn't as easy as it sounds.

44:31.001 --> 44:32.002
Why?

44:32.753 --> 44:34.463
Because people spread rumors.

44:36.632 --> 44:38.676
What exactly is your point?

44:41.470 --> 44:43.681
Well, it's nothing grand.

44:45.474 --> 44:46.892
But as you already know,

44:48.060 --> 44:49.103
there's something going on.

44:50.354 --> 44:51.397
So...

44:52.523 --> 44:53.857
if I were

44:54.650 --> 44:56.360
to support you,

44:59.571 --> 45:01.407
I need to be in a stable position.

45:02.658 --> 45:03.742
You know.

45:06.870 --> 45:09.706
Instead of just looking into our sales...

45:12.751 --> 45:13.961
You know what I mean.

45:16.004 --> 45:19.049
I'll try to look into what's going on.

45:21.009 --> 45:22.719
You're smart.

45:23.846 --> 45:26.515
You're really quick-witted.

45:54.418 --> 45:56.795
What would happen to the assailants
once we reveal the truth?

45:57.045 --> 45:58.088
They'll get fired, right?

45:59.715 --> 46:00.883
No way.

46:01.049 --> 46:03.469
You think it'll end with a punishment?
That can't happen.

46:03.927 --> 46:05.846
We need to fight for their dismissal.

46:06.930 --> 46:08.932
That's taking things a bit too far.

46:09.475 --> 46:11.685
They're all just trying to earn a living.

46:11.768 --> 46:12.728
And we aren't?

46:13.854 --> 46:15.189
Why are you getting all riled up?

46:16.190 --> 46:19.234
I just don't want the confrontation
to affect you negatively, that's all.

46:21.904 --> 46:23.113
Why are you excluding yourself?

46:24.823 --> 46:25.866
What are you talking about?

46:28.243 --> 46:29.745
Stop grilling me, okay?

46:32.748 --> 46:33.790
I'm off.

46:37.711 --> 46:38.795
That little...

46:56.813 --> 46:58.065
Is this really okay?

47:00.484 --> 47:01.860
Isn't this too expensive?

47:01.944 --> 47:03.820
Gosh, don't worry. Just eat up.

47:05.197 --> 47:08.242
Hey, I can afford to treat my colleague
to this kind of meal.

47:09.284 --> 47:10.619
Eat up. We can order more.

47:11.286 --> 47:14.122
Anyway, I have to say

47:15.082 --> 47:17.876
that I'm very proud of us
for coming this far.

47:19.503 --> 47:21.880
Well, we did get some help on the way.

47:23.131 --> 47:24.341
Who helped us?

47:25.509 --> 47:26.760
In your case,

47:26.843 --> 47:29.012
Mr. Nam has been
taking such great care of you.

47:32.266 --> 47:34.142
That's total bullshit.

47:34.977 --> 47:37.437
He can still be in that position
thanks to me.

47:40.148 --> 47:43.944
Right, you've been supporting him
in many aspects.

47:44.027 --> 47:45.153
That's not everything.

47:46.822 --> 47:49.908
Everyone will be screwed
if I open my mouth.

47:50.701 --> 47:51.868
Hey, do you remember?

47:52.244 --> 47:54.913
That girl who used to be in HR
and got married. What was her name?

47:55.706 --> 47:56.999
- Her name was--
- You see,

47:58.208 --> 47:59.585
only Mr. Nam could touch her.

48:01.628 --> 48:02.838
Is he that bad?

48:02.921 --> 48:05.841
I'm... I never really noticed it.

48:06.758 --> 48:09.595
You need to become
a better judge of character to succeed.

48:10.804 --> 48:11.888
There's more.

48:12.931 --> 48:16.018
You know that I recently went
on a business trip with Yoon Jin-a, right?

48:16.101 --> 48:18.645
- Yes.
- Even then... Gosh, don't get me started.

48:18.729 --> 48:21.940
Didn't he just tell you
to treat them to a meal?

48:24.026 --> 48:27.821
This is precisely why those
who hold themselves back are idiots.

48:29.865 --> 48:32.701
Let's be honest. I only did those things
when I got excited

48:33.201 --> 48:35.037
during our team dinners

48:35.120 --> 48:36.913
because we were having
so much fun together.

48:36.997 --> 48:38.707
Yes, that's right.

48:38.999 --> 48:41.960
But things got out of hand because
the female employees got the wrong idea.

48:42.044 --> 48:43.795
However, he's on a whole different level.

48:46.882 --> 48:49.426
Oh, I found it.
Gosh, you have to hear this.

48:50.093 --> 48:52.054
"We must finalize a deal that benefits us.

48:52.262 --> 48:55.682
It'd be a good idea to use Yoon Jin-a
to break the ice."

48:56.224 --> 48:58.977
Hey, he basically meant
that I should use her

48:59.061 --> 49:01.313
to lure them to give us what we need,
don't you think?

49:02.648 --> 49:03.690
Gosh, I'm...

49:05.609 --> 49:07.361
- I can't--
- Look, I'm not making it up.

49:10.822 --> 49:14.618
But Yoon Jin-a must have sensed
that something was up.

49:14.701 --> 49:15.994
She backed out of it.

49:16.078 --> 49:17.412
Gosh, that girl...

49:39.434 --> 49:42.020
Dad, what are you doing here?

49:42.104 --> 49:44.898
I've been waiting for you
so that I can take you out on a date.

50:00.622 --> 50:01.998
You must have something to tell me.

50:02.791 --> 50:03.625
What is it?

50:11.049 --> 50:12.926
I'm going to tell you something,

50:14.553 --> 50:15.804
but don't get the wrong idea.

50:19.266 --> 50:20.350
First and foremost,

50:21.226 --> 50:24.146
I want you to know that your mom
and I put you first in everything

50:25.147 --> 50:26.690
and that it's our duty to lead you

50:26.773 --> 50:28.483
to the right direction.

50:33.196 --> 50:35.198
I know that you're upset
with your mom, but...

50:35.699 --> 50:36.950
I'm not upset.

50:37.826 --> 50:39.161
I'm just disappointed.

50:40.454 --> 50:41.455
Right.

50:42.914 --> 50:45.083
But you can understand her, right?

50:45.417 --> 50:47.919
No, I can't understand her.

50:49.421 --> 50:50.797
Why doesn't she like Jun-hui?

50:51.131 --> 50:52.591
What's wrong with him?

50:53.467 --> 50:55.385
Nothing's wrong with him, but...

50:58.263 --> 51:00.098
I know that it's not right

51:00.515 --> 51:02.976
to judge people based on the environment

51:03.226 --> 51:05.353
they grew up in or what they have,

51:07.564 --> 51:11.234
but parental absence
has a huge impact on children.

51:12.569 --> 51:13.570
Dad.

51:14.863 --> 51:17.491
You can't overlook the importance
of parents in one's life.

51:18.533 --> 51:20.327
Even when you step into the real world,

51:21.578 --> 51:23.789
there are things that you must learn
from your parents.

51:26.291 --> 51:27.959
And when things are hard,

51:28.043 --> 51:31.046
your parents can give you advice
from their experience.

51:31.421 --> 51:33.507
That's how parents help you
grow and mature.

51:35.050 --> 51:36.468
Is Jun-hui a jerk?

51:39.221 --> 51:41.097
Is he rude or disrespectful toward elders?

51:41.181 --> 51:43.850
- No, he's not.
- Then what's the problem?

51:45.227 --> 51:47.312
There's no legitimate reason whatsoever.

51:49.064 --> 51:52.150
Do you think I'm loved by everyone
because I was brought up by you and Mom?

51:52.484 --> 51:53.777
Not at all.

51:54.528 --> 51:56.404
I guess both you and Mom

51:56.988 --> 51:58.615
are proud of me because I'm your daughter,

51:59.866 --> 52:01.993
but I'm nothing special.

52:02.994 --> 52:05.580
Actually, other people are far better
than me in some respects.

52:06.414 --> 52:07.415
Jun-hui?

52:08.416 --> 52:10.168
I'm more than grateful that he's with me.

52:11.336 --> 52:13.964
At times, I wonder if I really deserve
to be his girlfriend

52:14.464 --> 52:16.132
because he's such a wonderful person.

52:16.216 --> 52:19.177
Your perspective is different
from your mom's or mine.

52:24.516 --> 52:25.892
What's love?

52:37.153 --> 52:40.115
You said that it's the parents' job
to teach their children how to be better.

52:41.575 --> 52:43.326
Then tell me what love is.

52:52.586 --> 52:53.587
Dad.

53:01.845 --> 53:03.096
For the first time in my life,

53:04.598 --> 53:06.266
I'm learning what love is

53:07.642 --> 53:09.227
and how to love someone.

53:11.479 --> 53:13.231
I've been learning a lot from Jun-hui.

53:14.482 --> 53:16.401
Even everything I did for Mom
at the hospital...

53:17.527 --> 53:19.195
How I helped her get changed,

53:20.030 --> 53:21.615
put on her shoes,

53:21.990 --> 53:23.658
and get down from the bed...

53:24.618 --> 53:26.244
Even how I talked to her lovingly...

53:28.455 --> 53:31.124
He's always worried about me
falling or getting hurt.

53:32.125 --> 53:33.543
Even though I'm an adult,

53:35.337 --> 53:39.424
he's always anxious,
which shows how much he loves me.

53:41.176 --> 53:43.303
He's been pouring all his love on me,

53:44.054 --> 53:45.388
your daughter.

53:48.308 --> 53:51.061
Why can't you approve of a guy
who loves your daughter that much?

53:52.562 --> 53:54.314
How can you disapprove of him?

53:55.482 --> 53:57.484
He's such a warm-hearted person.

53:58.526 --> 54:00.111
He's very kind.

54:10.705 --> 54:12.165
I won't listen to you.

54:13.416 --> 54:16.086
I'll give up
only when I experience it myself

54:16.169 --> 54:17.629
and feel like it's not going to work.

54:18.421 --> 54:20.256
Until that happens,
I won't break up with him

54:20.340 --> 54:21.675
no matter what you say or do.

54:24.302 --> 54:25.720
I don't care if I disappoint you.

54:27.430 --> 54:29.432
I'm disappointed in you and Mom too.

55:12.517 --> 55:14.102
You left the store a while ago.

55:14.185 --> 55:15.645
Why aren't you home yet?

55:15.729 --> 55:16.771
Where are you now?

55:19.691 --> 55:21.026
Why do you sound so down?

55:23.486 --> 55:24.779
You're not feeling sick, are you?

55:27.490 --> 55:28.783
You can't get sick.

55:32.662 --> 55:34.122
Your voice sounds strange.

55:35.248 --> 55:37.542
My nose is stuffed up because it's cold.

55:38.501 --> 55:40.086
I guess you're not dressed warmly enough.

55:42.130 --> 55:44.382
I'm totally bundled up.

55:47.469 --> 55:48.887
Do you have to work all night again?

55:49.596 --> 55:52.557
No, we are almost done with the project.

55:53.141 --> 55:54.768
And here's my proposal.

55:55.727 --> 55:56.770
What is it?

55:57.270 --> 55:59.064
Let's cook something at home this weekend.

56:00.607 --> 56:02.358
I can't cook.

56:03.151 --> 56:04.652
I was worried that you might volunteer.

56:08.948 --> 56:09.991
So?

56:10.950 --> 56:12.660
What will you cook for me?

56:13.661 --> 56:16.164
I can make anything you want.

56:17.582 --> 56:18.792
Anything I want?

56:19.334 --> 56:20.418
Of course.

56:20.794 --> 56:23.129
I can do anything for you, Jin-a.

56:24.172 --> 56:25.465
What do you want?

56:29.677 --> 56:31.137
I want...

56:32.639 --> 56:33.681
I want you.

56:35.725 --> 56:37.435
All I want is you, Jun-hui.

56:50.448 --> 56:51.574
Why are you back alone?

56:53.076 --> 56:55.495
If you're that curious,
you should've just joined us.

56:57.747 --> 57:00.291
I don't want to repeat myself.
Ask Dad when he gets home.

57:00.792 --> 57:02.544
Make sure you're free this weekend.

57:03.545 --> 57:06.589
A friend of mine wants
to set you up with a guy.

57:10.802 --> 57:11.803
You're so childish

57:12.762 --> 57:14.722
to the point that it disgusts me.

57:20.270 --> 57:21.479
That brat...

57:36.995 --> 57:38.746
They're thoughtful enough, you know.

57:39.372 --> 57:42.125
Why don't we just leave them be
and see what happens?

57:43.126 --> 57:46.254
What if they become
too attached to each other?

57:47.130 --> 57:51.050
How can you make
such an irresponsible remark as her dad?

57:52.719 --> 57:56.222
They've already fallen for each other.
It's not like we can pull them apart.

57:56.639 --> 57:58.057
That's not how love works.

57:58.600 --> 58:00.393
What? Love?

58:00.977 --> 58:02.395
What the hell are you talking about?

58:02.645 --> 58:04.647
It's just because they've known
each other forever.

58:04.731 --> 58:07.108
It's definitely not love.

58:08.234 --> 58:10.028
Then what is love?
Do you even know what it is?

58:10.111 --> 58:11.738
Goodness.
Why don't you tell me what it is?

58:12.906 --> 58:14.073
I'm not telling you.

58:17.577 --> 58:20.747
- Gosh, we're not done talking.
- Just turn the lights off.

58:32.550 --> 58:33.676
Don't you dare step on me.

58:35.595 --> 58:36.763
I can see everything.

59:11.798 --> 59:14.342
Will the next game be about cooking?

59:14.634 --> 59:15.677
What are you talking about?

59:16.219 --> 59:17.845
Then why are you looking at cooking sites?

59:18.596 --> 59:22.267
I want to invite Jin-a over
and cook something for her this weekend.

59:23.810 --> 59:27.397
Why don't you do that for me?
Gosh, seriously.

59:27.772 --> 59:30.650
It's too early for you to get jealous.

59:30.775 --> 59:32.819
Are you trying to say
that it'll only get worse?

59:33.903 --> 59:35.321
You won't be able to handle it.

59:38.741 --> 59:39.742
Are you mad?

59:39.993 --> 59:41.911
Yes, I'm so mad right now.

59:41.995 --> 59:43.413
Come on. Cut me some slack.

59:43.496 --> 59:44.831
I can't!

59:47.000 --> 59:48.209
Have a good night.

01:01:04.327 --> 01:01:07.205
CANADA

01:01:21.886 --> 01:01:22.929
Hello?

01:01:24.555 --> 01:01:25.598
Hello?

01:01:26.099 --> 01:01:27.475
Yes, who is this?

01:01:30.645 --> 01:01:31.938
It's me, Gyeong-seon.

01:01:34.023 --> 01:01:35.858
Oh, hey. What's up?

01:01:37.902 --> 01:01:39.779
Do you have a moment to talk?

01:01:40.655 --> 01:01:42.782
- Right now?
- You can't talk now?

01:01:43.658 --> 01:01:46.619
Well... I'm out with my kid now.

01:01:47.995 --> 01:01:50.039
I'm your child too, Dad.

01:01:50.623 --> 01:01:53.501
Why do you say such a thing
out of the blue?

01:01:54.001 --> 01:01:55.795
Then what else
would you like me to talk about?

01:01:56.295 --> 01:01:58.047
Do you want me to wish you happiness?

01:01:58.589 --> 01:02:00.842
Or should I never call you again?

01:02:02.468 --> 01:02:03.511
Gosh...

01:02:06.848 --> 01:02:08.641
Do you even know
how many years it has been?

01:02:09.642 --> 01:02:13.646
Have you ever wondered
how Jun-hui and I are doing?

01:02:13.730 --> 01:02:14.897
All right.

01:02:15.481 --> 01:02:16.649
You say that all the time.

01:02:16.733 --> 01:02:19.485
Until when are you going to avoid us
like this?

01:02:20.945 --> 01:02:24.449
Should we really not expect
anything from you, Dad?

01:02:25.450 --> 01:02:26.826
Let's talk another time.

01:03:31.015 --> 01:03:33.476
I'm drinking so that I can fall asleep.

01:03:34.519 --> 01:03:35.853
Why can't you fall asleep?

01:03:36.979 --> 01:03:38.481
Because I miss you.

01:03:39.732 --> 01:03:41.484
It's just an excuse for you to drink.

01:03:43.027 --> 01:03:44.987
If I could, I'd show you

01:03:45.655 --> 01:03:47.490
how much I miss you right now.

01:03:48.658 --> 01:03:50.868
I miss you too.

01:03:52.578 --> 01:03:53.913
It's really killing me.

01:03:54.497 --> 01:03:55.873
I don't miss you that much.

01:03:59.836 --> 01:04:01.462
Don't grimace, okay?

01:04:03.005 --> 01:04:04.048
This is nice.

01:04:04.674 --> 01:04:05.758
What's nice?

01:04:07.426 --> 01:04:10.805
It's as if we can see each other
even when we're not together.

01:04:14.642 --> 01:04:15.601
I heard that.

01:04:18.813 --> 01:04:21.399
My boyfriend is drinking,

01:04:21.524 --> 01:04:23.776
so I figured I should drink too.

01:04:26.070 --> 01:04:27.947
I would've shut you up if you were here.

01:04:28.614 --> 01:04:29.657
With what?

01:04:30.616 --> 01:04:32.535
With what you're thinking right now.

01:04:35.246 --> 01:04:36.205
Count to ten, okay?

01:05:26.547 --> 01:05:27.590
Open the door.

01:07:45.352 --> 01:07:47.563
I don't think it's a mistake
that I decided to date Jin-a.

01:07:47.646 --> 01:07:49.732
You don't meet my standards.

01:07:49.940 --> 01:07:52.068
Why do you always say that you're okay?

01:07:52.151 --> 01:07:53.986
- Come here.
- You can get angry all you want.

01:07:54.070 --> 01:07:55.696
You can totally bad-mouth my mom.

01:07:55.780 --> 01:07:56.655
Yoon Jin-a is here.

01:07:56.739 --> 01:08:00.117
We're doing this for you.
You can't just keep backing out of it.

01:08:00.201 --> 01:08:01.368
Those whom Mr. Nam harassed...

01:08:01.452 --> 01:08:04.121
Gosh, Jin-a...

01:08:04.205 --> 01:08:05.998
Let's not betray each other.

01:08:06.499 --> 01:08:08.959
- Call me your brother-in-law. Stop.
- Brother-in-law, my foot.

01:08:09.043 --> 01:08:11.754
- He's my brother.
- He's my boyfriend!

01:08:11.837 --> 01:08:12.922
Dad's here.

01:08:13.005 --> 01:08:15.674
Who cares what he has to say?
I don't even want to listen to him.

01:08:15.800 --> 01:08:17.843
Who else would care this much about me?

01:08:17.927 --> 01:08:19.720
You always put up
with all the stress alone.

01:08:19.804 --> 01:08:20.971
Why did you lie to me? Why?

01:08:21.055 --> 01:08:24.225
Get off her. Right now!
I told you to get off her!

01:08:24.308 --> 01:08:25.643
Jin-a.

01:08:26.393 --> 01:08:27.895
I'm okay. I really am.

01:08:28.646 --> 01:08:29.772
I'm okay too.

01:08:30.731 --> 01:08:31.982
I can get through anything.

01:08:34.193 --> 01:08:36.112
Subtitle translation by Kim Su-hyeon
